-- Commonwealth Bank nabs top Credit Suisse banker
-- 
-- Thu Sep 15, 2011 8:00pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2011/09/16/us-cba-dealmaker-idUSTRE78F00120110916

 

 SYDNEY  (Reuters) - Commonwealth Bank of Australia (CBA) ( CBA.AX ) appointed several top executives on Friday, including a key Credit Suisse ( CSGN.VX ) dealmaker, highlighting its efforts to acquire top talent under its new chief executive. 

 CBA appointed Robert Jesudason, most recently a top mergers and acquisition banker for Credit Suisse in Hong Kong, to take over as group head of strategy. CBA's chief executive elect, Ian Narev, is himself a proven dealmaker and his move to hire a top M&A banker could indicate that CBA will increase its focus on takeover opportunities in Asia. The bank also picked Grahame Petersen has been appointed group executive business and private banking. (Reporting by  Balazs Koranyi ; Editing by  Mark Bendeich )